casebody.data:
January 27, 1961. No. 542,

Misc.

Barbone et al. v. United States. Petitioners pro se. Solicitor General Cox was on the stipulation for the United States. J. Lee Rankin, then Solicitor General, Acting Assistant Attorney General Foley, Beatrice Rosenberg and Julia P. Cooper were on the brief for the United States in opposition to the petition.

On petition for writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit. Petition dismissed pursuant to stipulation under Rule 60 of the Rules of this Court.
